cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the problem of multiple object tracking using detection responses. The use of a neural network to learn the solution to the Maximum Weighted Bipartite Matching problem suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The investigation of appearance and motion cues for object feature representation and pairwise affinities suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The use of a graph neural network to solve the combinatorial hardness of the matching problem suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the focus on the optimization module and the use of a bipartite graph suggests that it could belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
